ygData.subject: RE: [eqbards] Snare changes
ygData.msgSnippet: I hear from my other player friends that its just bards perhaps since the rangers haven t mentioned it yet in guildchat, for what that s worth.  Hard to talk
ygData.messageBody:
I hear from my other player friends that its just bards perhaps since the
rangers haven't mentioned it yet in guildchat, for what that's worth. Hard
to talk on the phone to people in L Guk on the east coast and get coherent
conversation. Possibly an undetected break in our songs due to the druid
changes to root and damage songs.

-----Original Message-----
From: Reece, Tom CPT- 25IDL G4
[mailto:g4mntofcr@...]
Sent: Tuesday, June 06, 2000 4:13 PM
To: eqbards@egroups.com
Subject: RE: [eqbards] Snare changes


Are you talking about the bard Selos Consonant Chain song or Snare spell
rangers and druids have?

Galtin
-----Original Message-----
From: Daryl Schwemley [mailto:drs@...]
Sent: Tuesday, June 06, 2000 11:47 AM
To: 'eqbards@egroups.com'
Subject: [eqbards] Snare changes


I've heard that Verant has changed our snares to no longer completely stop
mobs dead in their tracks. Might wanna be careful tonight guys.

Gilgurth
Bard of 24 Winces
E'ci
